# Data Talk — Comprehensive Project Analysis

> **Scope**: Full codebase audit of all 8 backend Python files (~2,400 lines), 4 frontend JavaScript files (~2,000 lines), 7 CSS modules, 3 HTML pages, and supporting configuration. Performed 2026-04-01.

---

## 1. Executive Summary

Data Talk is a **chat-based data analysis platform** that lets non-technical users upload CSV/Excel datasets and converse with an AI (Google Gemini) to generate insights, Plotly charts, statistical tables, and KPI dashboards — all without writing code. It is architected as a **monolithic Flask SPA** with Supabase for auth, storage, and persistence, and a vanilla JavaScript frontend.

**Bottom line**: The product concept is **genuinely strong** — it solves a real pain point (making data exploration accessible to non-coders). The multi-step LLM pipeline (extraction → code generation → execution → interpretation) is sophisticated and well beyond what most hobby projects achieve. However, the codebase has **accumulated architectural debt, security soft spots, and scalability ceilings** that would need serious attention before any production deployment, team onboarding, or feature expansion.

