## 3. Strengths ✅

### 3.1 Genuinely Innovative Multi-Step Pipeline
Most "chat with your data" tools either (a) send raw CSV to the LLM (token-expensive, inaccurate for large datasets) or (b) generate code with no safety net. Data Talk's pipeline is **significantly more sophisticated**:
- **Extraction step** pre-computes value distributions so the code-gen LLM has ground-truth data to work with
- **Data profiling** (`get_data_profile`) auto-detects dataset type (time series, transactional, survey, categorical, numerical) and injects domain-specific analysis suggestions into the prompt
- **Retry with error feedback** — failed code is sent back to Gemini with the traceback, mimicking a developer debugging cycle
- **Post-execution interpretation** — the raw computed results are re-sent to the LLM for human-readable explanation, separating "compute" from "explain"

This architecture produces **demonstrably better results** than a single-shot prompt approach.

### 3.2 Well-Designed Code Execution Sandbox
The `code_executor.py` has **multiple layers of protection**:
- **AST validation** with `_SafetyVisitor` — blocks imports, forbidden names, dangerous attributes, and blocked builtins at the syntax level
- **Restricted builtins** — `open`, `eval`, `exec`, `compile`, `__import__` etc. are all blocked
- **Forbidden module names** — `os`, `sys`, `subprocess`, `socket`, `pathlib`, `shutil`, `ctypes` etc.
- **Forbidden attributes** — `__class__`, `__bases__`, `__globals__`, `__subclasses__`, `system`, `popen`, etc.
- **Code length limit** (10,000 chars) — prevents the LLM from hardcoding entire datasets
- **Timeout guard** (60 seconds) — prevents infinite loops
- **Deep type conversion** (`_deep_convert`) — properly handles numpy/pandas types for JSON serialization

### 3.3 Clean Error Hierarchy
The `errors.py` module defines a proper exception hierarchy with `DataTalkError` as the base class. Each subclass carries its own HTTP status code and error type string, enabling the global `@app.errorhandler(DataTalkError)` to produce consistent JSON error responses automatically.

### 3.4 Per-User State Isolation
The `SessionManager` + `UserState` pattern in `app_state.py` properly isolates per-user caches, chat histories, and active files. Thread-safety is ensured with `threading.Lock`. The TTL-based eviction prevents unbounded memory growth.

### 3.5 Thoughtful Frontend UX Features
- **SSE streaming** for real-time phase updates during analysis (not just a spinner)
- **Follow-up question chips** generated by the AI
- **Chart annotation** — users can click data points and add text annotations
- **Fullscreen chart view** with focus trapping and keyboard accessibility
- **Chart customizer panel** — modify titles, axis labels, colors, scales, and legend position
- **GridStack drag-and-drop dashboard** with persistent layout saving
- **KPI stat cards** with multiple aggregation types
- **Data grid** powered by Handsontable with filtering, sorting, column resize

### 3.6 Proper Authentication Architecture
- Supabase Auth with JWT verification via `getUser()` (not just client-side token parsing)
- Service-role client for server-side operations that bypass RLS
- `@require_auth` decorator pattern for route protection
- Token in `Authorization: Bearer` header (not cookies)
- Profile data loaded from a separate `profiles` table

### 3.7 Good Developer Experience Choices
- Structured logging with `_log_event()` — machine-parseable JSON logs
- Token usage tracking for cost monitoring
- Configurable via environment variables with sensible defaults
- Self-signed HTTPS certificate auto-generation for local dev
- `start.bat` for one-click Windows launch

