## 8. Verdict

| Dimension | Grade | Notes |
|-----------|-------|-------|
| **Concept & Product Vision** | **A** | Solves a real problem elegantly; the "chat with your data" concept with code execution is well ahead of most competitors |
| **Backend Architecture** | **B-** | Multi-step pipeline is clever; but monolithic, in-memory, and has sandbox risks |
| **Frontend Architecture** | **C+** | Functional and feature-rich, but global-scope spaghetti with no module system or tests |
| **Security** | **C** | Auth is well-done; sandbox is the weakest link; no CSRF, incomplete rate limiting |
| **Scalability** | **D+** | In-memory state, no worker scaling, full-dataset endpoints — this is strictly a single-user local tool |
| **Code Quality** | **B** | Clean formatting, good docstrings, structured logging — but God Module, duplicate functions, and zero tests |
| **UX/UI** | **A-** | SSE streaming, chart annotations, GridStack dashboard, keyboard accessibility — genuinely premium feel |
| **DevOps** | **D** | No CI/CD, no tests, no migrations, no production server config |
| **Documentation** | **B+** | Excellent README with clear structure diagram, API table, and security note |

### Overall: **B- (Impressive prototype, not production-ready)**

The project demonstrates **strong product thinking and creative engineering** — particularly the multi-step LLM pipeline, the data profiling system, and the dashboard UX. For a solo developer building a capstone or portfolio project, this is genuinely impressive work.

The path to production readiness requires addressing: (1) the code execution sandbox, (2) state management for scaling, (3) comprehensive testing, and (4) decomposing the monolith. Of these, the sandbox and testing are the most urgent.
